BT 1 0 0 1 0 183 Tm /F1 9 Tf 12 TL (Water is not a passive solvent. It is a battery. Every interface in biology -- every membrane, every protein surface, every) Tj T* (microtubule wall -- creates an exclusion zone \(EZ\) where water self-organizes into a negatively charged, hexagonally) Tj T* (ordered phase \(H?O?\) separated from positively charged bulk water. This charge separation stores energy. The voltage) Tj T* (across the EZ boundary is approximately 100-200 mV \(Pollack, 2013; Chai et al., 2009\). Infrared light at 3.1 micrometers) Tj T* (charges this battery. The body contains approximately 15,000 m? of internal membrane surface area -- every square meter) Tj T* (a charging plate. The mitochondrial membrane sustains a proton gradient of ~180 mV across ~5 nm, producing an electric) Tj T* (field of 36 million V/m -- stronger than lightning. ATP synthase converts this gradient into mechanical rotation at ~9,000) Tj T* -0.116684 Tw (RPM with ~100% thermodynamic efficiency \(Yasuda et al., 2001\). The human body synthesizes ~40 kg of ATP per day from) Tj T* 0 Tw (water-mediated proton transport. Photosystem II splits water into protons, electrons, and oxygen using a Mn?CaO? cluster) Tj T* (that achieves quantum coherent energy transfer at room temperature \(Engel et al., 2007\). The electric eel stacks 6,000) Tj T* (water-based electrochemical cells to produce 860 V \(de Santana et al., 2019\). Every one of these systems runs on the) Tj T* (same principle: structured water at an interface creates charge separation, and the Grotthuss mechanism \(Principle 3\)) Tj T* (moves the charge. Water is not the medium life happens in. Water is the battery life runs on. This paper unifies EZ water) Tj T* (\(Pollack\), chemiosmotic theory \(Mitchell, Nobel 1978\), quantum biology \(Engel et al.\), and the Wike Coherence framework) Tj T* (into a single energy architecture: water at interfaces, near a phase transition, storing and transporting charge via proton) Tj T* (coherence.) Tj T* ET
